## New protocol shape

```ts
export type CloudAgentRunStatus =
  | "CREATING"
  | "RUNNING"
  | "FINISHED"
  | "CANCELLED"
  | "ERROR"
  | "EXPIRED";

export type AgentInboxStatus = "draft" | "queued" | "running" | "waiting" | "done" | "failed";
```

Map `CloudAgentRunStatus` → `AgentInboxStatus` for the HUD: `CREATING|RUNNING` → `running`, `FINISHED` → `done`, `CANCELLED|ERROR|EXPIRED` → `failed`. A run with an outstanding human question is `waiting`; we keep that mapping logic in shared code.

New shared types (rename `CursorSession` → `AgentSession`; do not preserve the old type for back-compat):

```ts
export type AgentSession = {
  id: string;             // local UUID for the inbox row
  cursorAgentId?: string; // bc-...
  latestRunId?: string;   // run-...
  title: string;
  prompt: string;
  repoUrl?: string;
  startingRef?: string;
  branchName?: string;
  model?: { id: string; params?: { id: string; value: string }[] };
  inboxStatus: AgentInboxStatus;
  runStatus?: CloudAgentRunStatus;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
  url?: string;           // cursor.com/agents?id=...
  summary?: string;
  outputTail: string[];
  questions: AgentQuestion[];
};
```

Also add a `VoiceCommand` discriminated union for slash commands (start with `/orchestrate` + a fallthrough `unknown`), and a `BridgeEvent` union covering `snapshot`, `session.updated`, `voice.transcript`, `voice.command`, `error`.

